<br>
The main gripe about mages is their realative uselessness in the end game.  High end mages are limited primarily to CoHing the raid party to spots and summoning mod rods.  Pets are generally not allowed because so many dungeons have pathing problems and the dangers of pet pulling aggro when fighting a fearing mob.<br>
<br>
All that aside though they are a great class.  You can solo effectively as well as add excellent damage output to a group and you have the best pets in the game.   <p>Aegon, 56 Troubadour of Vazaelle <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umrgoodkin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mr Goodkin </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/19/02 6:41:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm44.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=64.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mages on Firiona Vie</span><hr size=1> I would love a mage as a partner.  I need bandages and can't afford them<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
